PHYSICAL ACTIVITY:
=================
No heavy lifting for 48 hours (two days). Leave dressing in place for 48 hours (two days); once removed, may shower. No driving within 48 hours (two days) of either surgery or of using narcotic (prescription) pain medications.


 
DIETARY INSTRUCTIONS:
====================
No new dietary restrictions imposed by this procedure.


 
RESOURCES/FOLLOW-UP CARE:
========================



Follow-up specific to surgery:
Report to the Emergency Department here if you notice any large swelling, active (ongoing) bleeding, or severe pain in the groin or other area where the catheter had been placed for the procedure (i.e. where the dressing / bandage is located).
